50|$|Maveric's landing {{location}} is an operator-defined GPS location. When under manual <b>joystick</b> <b>control,</b> a button can be pressed {{to initiate a}} deep-stall landing. If the mission changes mid-flight, waypoint dragging-and-dropping allows Maveric to accept new instructions. Fail-safes ensure safe retrieval {{in the case of}} lost communication, lost GPS signal, or low battery.|$|E
50|$|The Access 303 {{is similar}} to the Access 2.3 of the same class. It has the same <b>joystick</b> <b>control,</b> as well as the high boom and the setup whereby the helm and crew are sat facing forwards. It also has the same {{electric}} servo-assisted drives, making it suitable for people with physical disabilities.|$|E
50|$|The game is <b>controlled</b> mostly via <b>joystick</b> and mouse. The <b>joystick</b> <b>controls</b> the {{directional}} {{movement of}} the character, and the mouse {{is used in the}} selection of weapons and items. Keyboard can be used to give input and zoom the view towards or away from the character.|$|R
