50|$|The Scout traces its lineage {{back to the}} Aeronca Champ, {{by way of the}} Citabria. Like the Citabria, the Scout {{features}} {{tandem seating}} and <b>joystick</b> <b>controls.</b> The fuselage and tail surfaces are constructed of welded metal tubing. The outer shape of the fuselage is created by a combination of wooden formers and longerons, covered with fabric. The cross-section of the metal fuselage truss is triangular, a design feature traceable to the earliest Aeronca C-2 design of the late 1920s.|$|R
